title: For Sale/Trade:  ORIGINAL M950 CALICO (SUPER HIGH CAPACITY PISTOL 50/100 ROUNDS)
location: CAMBRIDGE / NORTH BRANCH, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
This is an original M950 9mm pistol not the new post ban Liberty model. It is in like new condition with the original operator’s manual. The gun has fired very few rounds, probably less than 100. The action is a roller delayed blowback action which is also used by CETME and Heckler & Koch German military rifles. It produces very little barrel climb and recoil. It is quite reliable. The ejection port is out the bottom so it is totally ambidextrous. This model was made years ago, long before modern design plastic guns were in style. It was way ahead of its time in both design and function, to say nothing about the capacity. This unusual, rare gun can be part of your collection. It's sure to be a conversation piece. It's a trip to shoot. It is shown with the 50 round magazine attached.  Package includes the following:

Flash hider ($45)
Scope/laser mount ($90).
Shell catcher ($49) sling swivels.
50 round magazine ($99).
Two 100 round magazines ($302)
Smoke covers for the 50 round drum ($39)
Smoke cover for the 100 round drums ($78).  These covers let you see the shells in the loaded magazines
50 round loading tool that quickly loads the magazines

I would be willing to take partial trade on 308 (7.62x51) ammo or Eotech optics.  Let me know what you have.

title: For Sale:  .45 Auto Rim +P Ammo - 255 gr. H.C. F.N. (1,000 fps/ M.E. 566 ft. lbs) - 20 Round Box
postcontent:
You've been asking for a couple +P 45 AUTO RIM loads for a long time, so by popular demand, here they are. Both loads are using high quality Starline brass. We've also incorporated a flash suppressed powder so you can shoot in the dark without blinding yourself and this is important because over 95% of all civilian shootings in the USA occur in low light when the criminal element is at work. Both of these loads are the equivalent of +P+ 45 ACP ammo or as it is also known, 45 Super. These are very stout loads, but will not harm modern 45 ACP revolvers, nor will these loads harm any post war 45 ACP revolvers. Feel free to safely shoot these loads in any post war 45 ACP revolver that is in normal good operating condition.

Check out the below velocities fired from personal real world revolvers, NOT test barrels. You'll notice that the new S&W 4 inch Mt. Gun gives speeds almost as fast as the older S&W revolvers with 5.5 and 6.5 inch barrels. This is NOT a typo. It simply shows that the new S&W revolvers are made to much tighter tolerances than the older S&W revolvers and therefore give higher velocities per inch of barrel. Also, we are aware that the 1937 manufactured model 1917 we used as a test gun, (see below velocity chart) is not post war.

Item # 32A - 255gr. hard cast flat nose bullet
S&W Mountain Gun, 4 inch bbl = 1031 FPS
S&W Model 325 (scandium) 2.5 inch bbl = 945 FPS
S&W model 1917 (1937 Production) 5.5 inch bbl = 1043 FPS
S&W 1955 Target (25-2) 6.5 inch bbl = 1070 FPS

Item # 32A - was designed for deep penetration with no bullet expansion. It will shoot right through stick frame and drywall construction walls and through both doors on a 2003 Dodge Ram or through a black bears skull, etc. It was designed for, among other things, outdoor use including black bear protection. Expect around 30 inches of penetration on live flesh and bone.

B.E.A.R. (Brown Enhanced Automatic Rifle) models from Adcor Defense feature a patent-bearing, gas piston system with a free-float barrel for increased accuracy. This is due to the piston's incorporation into the upper half of the forward rail system - so it never touches the barrel. Extremely close machine tolerances eliminate the need for piston rings. The B.E.A.R. offers a multi-position gas regulator with a removable gas tube. The piston's cyclical rate adjusts with a turn of the gas plug located in the front piston assembly. Because diminished heat reaches the upper, hot gases and carbon particulates are prevented from entering the receiver, lubricant lasts longer and maintenance is simplified. Due to superior design, the B.E.A.R. has no carrier tilt and low fouling of the chamber and action. The ejection port wiper prevents the entry of dust, sand and other debris by moving into the ejection port opening flush with the inside geometry of the upper receiver. The spring loaded shield allows the bolt carrier to return to ready position. Being made of a highly durable, self-lubricating polymer helps the shield withstand temperature extremes. The original B.E.A.R. AR-15 carbine features a 16" chrome-lined barrel from Green Mountain, button-broached with a 1:7 twist. It has a two-piece key-locked, highly-rigid quad-rail system made of aircraft-grade 7075-T6 aluminum alloy that seamlessly mounts to the upper receiver which is made from the same aircraft-grade 7075-T6 aluminum alloy. The upper and lower rails separate with the push of a button - no special tools required. The B.E.A.R. has an adjustable stock which goes from 36.25" down to 32.5," and overall total weight is 7.05 lbs. These models include both the standard AR-15 rear charging handle and a forward, ambidextrous charging handle which is cleverly hidden in a recess on the receiver. It is available optics-ready featuring Magpul MBUS front and rear folding sights. With a toolless field strip design, a B.E.A.R. requires nothing more than a firing pin to disassemble, yet remains strong.

The P-64 is a blowback operated, double-action pistol. Although designed from scratch by Polish engineers, the P-64 is very similar to German Walther PPK and is sometimes described erroneous in western literature as it's clone.

Frame and slide are made of steel and the finish is blue. The barrel is fixed to the frame with the recoil spring wound around it. The controls consist of a slide mounted safety lever and a magazine catch. The safety lever has two positions: up for "fire" and down for "safe" and decocks the hammer (if cocked) when put on safe. The safety mechanism allows the slide to be operated with safety on. Unlike the Walther, the P-64's magazine release is located at the bottom of the frame. The single-column magazines hold 6 rounds. The slides locks back when the last round from the magazine is fired but there is no external slide release. Double-action/Single Action. The sights are fixed.  A loaded-chamber indicator is located in the rear part of the slide, just above the hammer. Grips are checkered black plastic.

title: For Sale:  Glock 19 9mm w/ night sights
postcontent:
This is a 3rd generation Glock 19 9mm pistol with factory Glock night sights that were professionally installed less than a month ago.  It comes with (2) 15rd magazines, the original factory case, manual, fired casing from the factory (dated July 2006), and an uninstalled Glock OEM extended magazine release.  As you can see, I do have a Glock OEM extended slide release installed, which is a great addition to a Glock pistol and allows for much easier manipulation than the very flat and small standard one.

This pistol was manufactured prior to Glock switching to MIM internals, and many people on the gun forums feel that the non-MIM Glocks are superior and more durable.  You can easily tell that this is a non-MIM pistol by looking at the locking block in the frame.

This pistol is in beautiful condition and the only reason I'm selling is because I've switched over to the Gen 4 pistols because I prefer the more aggressive grip.  I can text additional photos to you if you would like.

Oddly, most of the changes that identify the Model 1884 as a distinct model occurred either before or after 1884. The Model 1884 incorporated a significant number of improvements that had been made between 1878 and 1879. It also featured a serrated trigger that had been incorporated into the Springfield rifle design in 1883.

title: For Sale:  Springfield 1911 45acp
For Sale:  600 Rounds Federal HST .40S&W JHP
postcontent:
Best CCW Ammo you can buy!

I do have more of this ammunition if you would like up to 800 rounds. If so I can make a better deal on it. 
For sale is 600 rounds of Federal HST 155gr JHP for a .40S&W. Federal released its Hydra-Shok line of ammunition to capture the law enforcement market years ago, and while it was a good round - it proved troublesome when going through barriers before reaching its target - clogging much of the time.

Federal corrected the problem by introducing a line known as HST, and it was tested extensively by the FBI upon its release in .40 caliber, and adopted as their ammunition after blowing the tests out of the water. This is currently the only ammunition I will carry as I feel like it is the only ammunition to hold a candle to the famous "Black Talon".

It's easy to find the much less desirable Hydra-Shok ammunition on the shelf, and many people are intrigued by the "post" inside the hollow point. If you do the research, and I suggest you do, you will find that HST is extremely tough to beat.

That's why HST has almost never (in my experience) been for sale on the shelves at your local gun shop - I have only ever found it online, for a premium price, and in small or limited quantities. I have recently switched to a different caliber for my preferred CCW and cannot find anywhere that sells HST in bulk, must less a place with a single box in stock right now.

I live in Puyallup, but will be willing to drive a reasonable distance to meet - or even ship if you want to pay for shipping.

Take a look here for FBI Protocol test results on this ammunition
http://le.atk.com/ammunition/federal/handgun/details.aspx?id=567

title: For Sale:  .22LR 6,000 rounds! could be yours!
postcontent:
Selling my supply of .22 long rifle. As stated in the title, I have 6,000 rounds I am selling in one package. At this time I am not interested in partial sales or trades, the price is cash only for the whole lot. 3,800 of it is Remington Thunderbolt 40 gr. lead round nose (This is sweet shooting ammo) and 2,200 of it is Remington Golden Bullet 36 gr. brass plated hp. I bought all of these during a similar ammo shortage at premium prices in the Fall of 2009. I am only selling because I was recently laid off and money is getting tight around the holidays, bad timing. So unfortunately it must go. Take advantage of a great (and quite frankly rare, considering the dismal state of ammo availability) opportunity to buy 6,000 rounds at once without online gouging or shipping costs. Willing to meet you in and around the Beaverton/ Tigard area. A perfect X-Mas or holiday gift for the .22 enthusiast or add to your own cache! 

As you can see in the photos, I have removed all from the original packaging and sorted them out into Ziploc bags of about 200 each. My idea was it is convenient for range trips and long term storage.

Let's get to the price. I'm asking $425 for everything. That is about 7 cents per round. I encourage you to see if you could find a similar price with this quantity and without shipping cost incurred from ordering online. I scoured it myself and came up with nothing, if you can even FIND 6k of .22lr available at all. I genuinely believe this to be a fair price all things considering, so I am relatively firm on that figure, but I will entertain other offers as necessary. 

I will try to respond to serious buyers as soon as I can. If I receive a lot of emails, I will just go down in order until I find a buyer, to be fair. If I don't reply by the end of the day its probably because I already sold it. 

Anyway, thanks for your interest and let me know if you want it!!
